<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496812>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Terminology used for species description of Phyllodoce. Morphology of parapodial cirri in anterior view: A, dorsal cirrus lanceolate; ventral cirrus rounded; B, dorsal cirrus lanceolate with tapered distal end; ventral cirrus elongated; C, dorsal cirrus cordiform; ventral cirrus lanceolate; D, dorsal cirrus quadrangular to rounded; ventral cirrus long and slender; E, dorsal cirrus cordiform; F, dorsal cirrus rounded, supracicular lobe digitiform. Abbreviations: Cir, cirrophore; deCir, dorsal extension of the cirrophore; Dc, dorsal cirrus; Lob, lobe, Vc, ventral cirrus. Scale Bars: A, 0.04 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C, 0.2 mm; D, 0.1 mm; E, 0.1 mm; F, 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4496812/files/figure.png" .

